FG-456 — Merits “If/Then” OA Pivots
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Pre-write pivot lines: If asked X → Then close Y.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Rows: Q signal • Std • Pin • Relief. Memorize; deliver with cadence.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft 5 pivot lines today.
	•	✅ Model Response: “If harmless error: Std—abuse; Pin Dkt 18:2; Relief—remand 21d.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Pivot scripts create confidence.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A switchboard routing Qs to one relief strip.

